1
00:00:08,291 --> 00:00:09,833
My name is Mai Taniyama,

2
00:00:09,916 --> 00:00:11,750
and I'm a freshman
in high school...

3
00:00:11,833 --> 00:00:13,458
Another mysterious case

4
00:00:13,541 --> 00:00:15,791
was brought to
Shibuya Psychic Research.

5
00:00:15,875 --> 00:00:18,791
A girl believed that her
friend was possessed by a fox,

6
00:00:18,875 --> 00:00:20,541
and a teacher
collapsed after claiming

7
00:00:20,625 --> 00:00:21,916
he could see ghosts.

8
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:23,625
After the principal
visited us

9
00:00:23,708 --> 00:00:27,000
we agreed to investigate the
events at Yuasa High School.

10
00:00:27,083 --> 00:00:29,416
When we got there weird
things kept happening,

11
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:32,583
and the stories got
stranger and scarier.

12
00:00:32,666 --> 00:00:35,416
What in the world
is going on here?

13
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:36,875
We did discover
an incident

14
00:00:36,958 --> 00:00:38,500
about three
months earlier...

15
00:00:38,583 --> 00:00:41,375
a girl named Kasai was
publicly ridiculed by teachers

16
00:00:41,458 --> 00:00:42,708
for saying she
could bend spoons

17
00:00:42,791 --> 00:00:45,041
using supernatural powers.

18
00:00:45,125 --> 00:00:46,333
And then...

19
00:00:46,416 --> 00:00:48,291
I'll curse you to death!

20
00:00:48,375 --> 00:00:49,958
Not long After that,

21
00:00:50,041 --> 00:00:53,791
the unexplainable and dangerous
occurrences started happening.

22
00:00:53,875 --> 00:00:55,666
And poor Miss Kei
was treated horribly

23
00:00:55,750 --> 00:00:56,916
by the other teachers

24
00:00:57,000 --> 00:00:59,208
just because she had
the nerve to defend me!

25
00:00:59,291 --> 00:01:01,291
I don't understand why
this is happening to me...

26
00:01:02,583 --> 00:01:05,208
I have a really bad
feeling about all of this.

27
00:01:05,291 --> 00:01:08,416
Underneath all of these
strange and mysterious events,

28
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:09,916
I sense a
creeping darkness

29
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:11,875
that's growing
stronger every day.

30
00:01:13,250 --> 00:01:18,958
[Music]

31
00:02:53,958 --> 00:02:56,500
On sunba nisunba
un bazaar un hatta,

32
00:02:56,583 --> 00:02:58,500
jaku un ban koku,

33
00:02:58,583 --> 00:03:01,416
on dakini shara
kyara heigi yaya.

34
00:03:04,208 --> 00:03:06,083
Drive them out
and purify.

35
00:03:06,166 --> 00:03:08,416
I entreat you
in serenity...

36
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:10,125
please receive
this humble prayer

37
00:03:10,208 --> 00:03:11,833
and grant my fervent wish.

38
00:03:13,333 --> 00:03:15,375
Our holy Father who
art in heaven...

39
00:03:16,791 --> 00:03:18,083
Hallowed be thy name.

40
00:03:24,875 --> 00:03:26,666
Nothing out of
the ordinary.

41
00:03:26,750 --> 00:03:28,916
No remarkable temperature
changes to report either.

42
00:03:30,583 --> 00:03:31,958
Of course not.

43
00:03:32,041 --> 00:03:34,291
Because there are no
spirits in this building.

44
00:03:34,375 --> 00:03:37,333
There are still unexplained
events happening here...

45
00:03:37,416 --> 00:03:39,500
it is imperative
keep investigating

46
00:03:39,583 --> 00:03:41,291
until we determine
their cause...

47
00:03:41,375 --> 00:03:42,250
Fine.

48
00:03:42,333 --> 00:03:43,666
But no matter
how hard you look

49
00:03:43,750 --> 00:03:45,083
you won't find spirits.

50
00:03:56,666 --> 00:03:58,958
So many foxfires,

51
00:03:59,041 --> 00:04:01,083
burning all over
the building...

52
00:04:01,166 --> 00:04:02,291
was it a dream?

53
00:04:02,375 --> 00:04:03,916
Or could it be...

54
00:04:07,750 --> 00:04:09,291
Wake up Mai!

55
00:04:09,375 --> 00:04:11,000
That was so weird...

56
00:04:11,083 --> 00:04:13,333
I've got a really bad
feeling about this.

57
00:04:14,583 --> 00:04:16,583
I hope everyone can do
their exorcisms fast

58
00:04:16,666 --> 00:04:18,291
so we can get out of here.

59
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:29,375
Kasai?

60
00:04:29,458 --> 00:04:31,000
Uh, wait a second!

61
00:04:31,083 --> 00:04:32,375
Kasai!

62
00:04:32,458 --> 00:04:33,500
Yeah?

63
00:04:33,583 --> 00:04:35,583
Um, well, can I help
you with anything?

64
00:04:35,666 --> 00:04:36,666
No thanks.

65
00:04:36,750 --> 00:04:38,208
Oh.

66
00:04:38,291 --> 00:04:40,583
Are all those other
people friends of yours?

67
00:04:40,666 --> 00:04:42,125
Huh?

68
00:04:42,208 --> 00:04:44,416
It looks like they're trying
to do some sort of exorcism.

69
00:04:44,500 --> 00:04:46,250
Oh... them, yeah

70
00:04:46,333 --> 00:04:48,458
Monk, Ayako and John are
my friends I guess...

71
00:04:48,541 --> 00:04:50,708
but actually they're
more like my coworkers.

72
00:04:50,791 --> 00:04:53,291
And Masako Hara?

73
00:04:53,375 --> 00:04:54,416
Ohh...

74
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:56,166
of course you'd
know who she is.

75
00:04:56,250 --> 00:04:58,625
I keep forgetting that Masako
is actually kinda famous.

76
00:04:58,708 --> 00:05:01,333
Yeah, I saw her on tv.

77
00:05:01,416 --> 00:05:03,791
What has she said
about this school?

78
00:05:03,875 --> 00:05:06,125
That there are a lot of
evil spirits hanging around?

79
00:05:06,208 --> 00:05:08,541
Uh-uh, actually she doesn't
think that there are any.

80
00:05:08,625 --> 00:05:09,958
Aren't any...?

81
00:05:10,041 --> 00:05:13,000
Even with all of the
stuff happening here?

82
00:05:13,083 --> 00:05:14,916
It was hard for me
to believe, too...

83
00:05:15,750 --> 00:05:17,833
but she swears she
doesn't see them here.

84
00:05:17,916 --> 00:05:18,916
So what about you?

85
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:20,166
Are you able to see them?

86
00:05:20,250 --> 00:05:22,791
Oh, no no no no
no no no, not me,

87
00:05:22,875 --> 00:05:24,041
I'm not a spiritualist.

88
00:05:24,125 --> 00:05:26,125
I've never been
able to do that.

89
00:05:26,208 --> 00:05:27,416
What about Mr. Shibuya?

90
00:05:27,500 --> 00:05:29,333
He's a spiritualist, right?

91
00:05:29,416 --> 00:05:30,791
Oh, Nar...

92
00:05:30,875 --> 00:05:33,583
I mean Mr. Shibuya isn't really
a spiritualist per se...

93
00:05:33,666 --> 00:05:35,541
he's more of a
Ghost Hunter...

94
00:05:35,625 --> 00:05:37,666
And I think he may be
an onmyouji as well.

95
00:05:37,750 --> 00:05:39,708
Is he really...?!

96
00:05:39,791 --> 00:05:43,500
So that would mean he
does practice onmyodo...

97
00:05:43,583 --> 00:05:45,000
Naru!

98
00:05:49,541 --> 00:05:50,625
See ya later?

99
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:19,625
I thought there was something
fishy about that girl.

100
00:06:19,708 --> 00:06:21,750
You're saying she came in here
to check us all out, right?

101
00:06:21,833 --> 00:06:24,041
Maybe she wasn't
checking us out,

102
00:06:24,125 --> 00:06:26,333
maybe she was just
curious or something.

103
00:06:26,416 --> 00:06:28,708
Well, Kasai is aware that
the whole school thinks

104
00:06:28,791 --> 00:06:30,541
her curse is the cause
of all of this...

105
00:06:30,625 --> 00:06:32,250
maybe she thinks
we believe it too

106
00:06:32,333 --> 00:06:34,166
and we're her latest
enemy, y'know?

107
00:06:34,250 --> 00:06:35,708
She wouldn't do that!

108
00:06:35,791 --> 00:06:37,750
Still... she does have powers...

109
00:06:37,833 --> 00:06:39,875
According to a number
of her schoolmates,

110
00:06:39,958 --> 00:06:42,875
she was apparently able to
bend spoons with her mind...

111
00:06:42,958 --> 00:06:45,958
do you think it's possible
she also possesses PK-LT?

112
00:06:46,041 --> 00:06:47,916
What's PK-LT?

113
00:06:48,875 --> 00:06:51,416
I'll explain it
for Mai's sake.

114
00:06:51,500 --> 00:06:54,458
PK-LT is the power to
affect living creatures

115
00:06:54,541 --> 00:06:56,541
using only a
force of will...

116
00:06:56,625 --> 00:06:58,708
the two major divisions
of supernatural ability

117
00:06:58,791 --> 00:07:01,041
are PK and ESP...

118
00:07:01,125 --> 00:07:04,000
or extra-sensory
perception.

119
00:07:04,083 --> 00:07:05,833
This is a special
ability to know things

120
00:07:05,916 --> 00:07:08,125
that normal people
wouldn't sense...

121
00:07:08,208 --> 00:07:10,875
Telepathy and clairvoyance
are in this category.

122
00:07:10,958 --> 00:07:13,625
PK, however, is a
force of will...

123
00:07:13,708 --> 00:07:17,041
moving objects by literally
thinking them into action...

124
00:07:17,125 --> 00:07:19,291
The three categories
are PK-MT...

125
00:07:19,375 --> 00:07:20,708
PK-ST...

126
00:07:20,791 --> 00:07:23,125
and last but
not least PK-LT.

127
00:07:25,583 --> 00:07:29,291
PK-ST is the power to
affect static targets...

128
00:07:29,375 --> 00:07:30,875
spoon-bending
would fall here.

129
00:07:32,250 --> 00:07:35,291
PK-MT is the power to
affect moving targets.

130
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:38,958
And PK-LT, as I've said,

131
00:07:39,041 --> 00:07:41,166
is the power to
affect living targets.

132
00:07:42,416 --> 00:07:43,791
So, what makes
you think Kasai

133
00:07:43,875 --> 00:07:45,666
is capable of
doing such a thing?

134
00:07:45,750 --> 00:07:47,000
If you can't see
the connection

135
00:07:47,083 --> 00:07:49,708
after everything I've said
then I can't help you.

136
00:07:49,791 --> 00:07:51,916
I'm sorry I'm so
stupid, your highness!

137
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:53,500
Are we in agreement

138
00:07:53,583 --> 00:07:56,333
then that Kasai really did
invoke a curse on the school?

139
00:07:56,416 --> 00:07:57,208
A curse?!

140
00:07:57,291 --> 00:07:58,750
She admitted it.

141
00:07:58,833 --> 00:08:00,625
She said "I'll
curse you to death!"

142
00:08:00,708 --> 00:08:01,875
Oh, right.

143
00:08:01,958 --> 00:08:03,916
But it's not
really a curse.

144
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,333
It's more like using
psychic powers

145
00:08:05,416 --> 00:08:06,583
to make people suffer...

146
00:08:06,666 --> 00:08:08,875
that's the PK-LT part...

147
00:08:08,958 --> 00:08:11,000
But judging from what I've
heard from a number of students

148
00:08:11,083 --> 00:08:13,875
I don't think the girl
has that much power.

149
00:08:13,958 --> 00:08:15,166
Do you guys
know about the

150
00:08:15,250 --> 00:08:18,375
famous British psychic
Oliver Davis?

151
00:08:18,458 --> 00:08:22,708
They say he can slam an l
aluminum block into the wall...

152
00:08:22,791 --> 00:08:25,833
But he hasn't been
able to perform PK-LT.

153
00:08:25,916 --> 00:08:28,916
This girl can't even seem
to bend spoons very well.

154
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:33,875
I remember when
I was little

155
00:08:33,958 --> 00:08:35,708
there was sort of a
supernatural craze,

156
00:08:35,791 --> 00:08:36,916
where tons of kids claimed

157
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:39,291
they could bend spoons
and perform magic...

158
00:08:39,375 --> 00:08:40,375
Of course It turned out

159
00:08:40,458 --> 00:08:41,958
that most of them
were just lying.

160
00:08:42,041 --> 00:08:44,291
Wow... that means you
must be pretty old.

161
00:08:48,291 --> 00:08:50,125
Be that as it may...

162
00:08:50,208 --> 00:08:52,625
It's very important to
remember that in Kasai's case

163
00:08:52,708 --> 00:08:55,291
she truly believed
in her psychic powers.

164
00:08:55,375 --> 00:08:57,750
She felt that she was unfairly
attacked and ridiculed

165
00:08:57,833 --> 00:09:00,833
by her teachers in front
of the entire school...

166
00:09:00,916 --> 00:09:02,583
And then...

167
00:09:02,666 --> 00:09:04,250
I'll curse you to death!

168
00:09:05,916 --> 00:09:08,458
Strange things began happening
after she said that.

169
00:09:09,500 --> 00:09:10,583
Those are the facts...

170
00:09:10,666 --> 00:09:12,875
and we can't ignore them.

171
00:09:12,958 --> 00:09:14,791
Something awful
has happened!

172
00:09:14,875 --> 00:09:16,958
Mr. oshino was in
a bad car accident

173
00:09:17,041 --> 00:09:18,166
and now he's in
the hospital!

174
00:09:28,166 --> 00:09:30,291
I... I was driving...

175
00:09:31,458 --> 00:09:34,000
And there it was,
right in front of me...

176
00:09:39,375 --> 00:09:40,541
It's because of her...

177
00:09:40,625 --> 00:09:41,708
that girl...

178
00:09:41,791 --> 00:09:43,833
it's Chiaki Kasai...

179
00:09:43,916 --> 00:09:45,541
When I was
leaving school...

180
00:09:45,625 --> 00:09:47,250
she ran into me...

181
00:09:47,333 --> 00:09:49,666
and she gave me the most
evil look I've ever seen!

182
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:54,041
Oh my God she
cursed me...!

183
00:09:54,125 --> 00:09:57,125
She cursed me to die and now
it's really happening...

184
00:10:02,250 --> 00:10:03,750
What do you think, Naru?

185
00:10:03,833 --> 00:10:05,291
Was it Kasai?

186
00:10:05,375 --> 00:10:06,791
I'm really not sure ...

187
00:10:06,875 --> 00:10:08,125
but we can safely say

188
00:10:08,208 --> 00:10:10,375
that things seem to
be getting worse.

189
00:10:10,458 --> 00:10:11,666
Let's hurry back...

190
00:10:11,750 --> 00:10:13,916
we've got a lot to do
and no time to waste.

191
00:10:16,583 --> 00:10:17,541
What's wrong?

192
00:10:17,625 --> 00:10:18,833
I don't know...

193
00:10:18,916 --> 00:10:20,875
I just felt scared
all of a sudden.

194
00:10:22,541 --> 00:10:24,750
C'mon, Kasai, admit it!

195
00:10:24,833 --> 00:10:26,208
Why don't you just stop!

196
00:10:26,291 --> 00:10:29,375
Yeah, stop using your
psychic powers or whatever...

197
00:10:29,458 --> 00:10:31,791
what're you trying to do,
scare everyone to death?!

198
00:10:31,875 --> 00:10:33,583
No... You're wrong.

199
00:10:33,666 --> 00:10:35,916
You know, if poor
Mr. oshino had died

200
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:38,916
you'd totally be
guilty of murder!

201
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:40,958
Hey, maybe we
should lay off...

202
00:10:41,041 --> 00:10:42,708
if we say too much
she could freak out

203
00:10:42,791 --> 00:10:45,208
and decide to
curse us next!

204
00:10:45,291 --> 00:10:47,208
What are you girls doing?

205
00:10:47,291 --> 00:10:48,666
Kasai?

206
00:10:53,875 --> 00:10:54,875
Kasai?!

207
00:10:55,833 --> 00:10:57,291
There they go again.

208
00:10:57,375 --> 00:10:58,875
It's kinda sick.

209
00:10:58,958 --> 00:11:00,541
I don't understand
how Miss Ubusuna

210
00:11:00,625 --> 00:11:02,208
can stick up for
her like that.

211
00:11:05,708 --> 00:11:07,458
Don't pay any
attention to them.

212
00:11:07,541 --> 00:11:08,708
It's not your fault.

213
00:11:08,791 --> 00:11:10,291
You've done nothing wrong.

214
00:11:20,083 --> 00:11:23,166
On sunba nisunba
un bazaar un hatta.

215
00:11:25,375 --> 00:11:28,041
The Word was made
flesh and was life...

216
00:11:28,125 --> 00:11:30,208
And that life was
the light of man.

217
00:11:30,291 --> 00:11:32,958
Naumaku san manda
botan on dakini.

218
00:11:35,416 --> 00:11:38,875
Praise be given as the gods
from all corners come together.

219
00:11:38,958 --> 00:11:41,416
On dakini shara
kyara heigi yaya ...

220
00:11:41,500 --> 00:11:43,666
The Word was made
flesh and was life...

221
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:49,375
Naumaku san manda
bazarandan kan!

222
00:11:49,458 --> 00:11:52,250
Man, they've got their
hands full with this one.

223
00:11:52,333 --> 00:11:54,708
They exorcized the track
team's locker room,

224
00:11:54,791 --> 00:11:56,083
as well as that desk,

225
00:11:56,166 --> 00:11:59,041
so they've hit every place
related to the incidents.

226
00:11:59,125 --> 00:12:01,791
But still I...

227
00:12:01,875 --> 00:12:03,291
I wonder if...

228
00:12:03,375 --> 00:12:04,750
I mean I hope nothing's...

229
00:12:04,833 --> 00:12:07,000
gonna pop out in
this room, too.

230
00:12:13,791 --> 00:12:15,125
Naru!

231
00:12:17,666 --> 00:12:19,291
Oh, how about I
make some tea?

232
00:12:19,375 --> 00:12:20,583
Fine.

233
00:12:22,708 --> 00:12:23,916
Hey, Naru?

234
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:25,583
I have a question
about Kasai...

235
00:12:25,666 --> 00:12:26,833
I don't know yet.

236
00:12:26,916 --> 00:12:28,166
Okay!

237
00:12:28,250 --> 00:12:30,416
It's just that there's
something bothering me.

238
00:12:33,250 --> 00:12:34,166
What's that?

239
00:12:34,250 --> 00:12:35,166
Did you see it?

240
00:12:37,916 --> 00:12:39,458
Aww, I hope it's
not a power outage.

241
00:12:39,541 --> 00:12:40,833
Quiet.

242
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:56,791
Now don't make any
sudden movements...

243
00:12:56,875 --> 00:12:58,291
Just stay calm.

244
00:13:12,625 --> 00:13:14,750
It's coming toward us...

245
00:13:14,833 --> 00:13:16,833
I'm so scared,

246
00:13:16,916 --> 00:13:18,916
oh somebody please help!

247
00:13:21,083 --> 00:13:22,916
Naumaku san manda
bazarandan kan!

248
00:13:31,250 --> 00:13:33,041
Ah, so the spirits
have started

249
00:13:33,125 --> 00:13:35,083
showing their faces
in here, too, huh.

250
00:13:35,166 --> 00:13:36,166
Apparently.

251
00:13:38,791 --> 00:13:40,416
Hey, are you alright, Mai?

252
00:13:40,500 --> 00:13:43,541
That woman never looked
at me, not once...

253
00:13:43,625 --> 00:13:44,875
she only looked at Naru!

254
00:13:44,958 --> 00:13:47,416
Mai, snap out of it.

255
00:13:47,500 --> 00:13:49,375
That spirit was
looking for Naru!

256
00:13:49,458 --> 00:13:50,833
Naru?

257
00:13:50,916 --> 00:13:52,041
That woman just now...

258
00:13:52,125 --> 00:13:53,416
It wasn't a coincidence,

259
00:13:53,500 --> 00:13:55,333
I know she came for him.

260
00:13:55,416 --> 00:13:57,166
I had a dream last night...

261
00:13:57,250 --> 00:13:59,333
and I saw foxfires
